The paper focuses on studying geotagging behavior on Twitter, which involves analyzing large-scale social media data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also touches upon topics such as public opinion inference and location prediction systems, which fall under the categories of cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively. Additionally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze the content of tweets, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the privacy and security implications of geotagging, which falls under the category of cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
